fbpFilter.description:
Filter for shipments delivered from partner warehouse (FBP). You can pass one of the following values:

- `ALL`—all shipments matching other filters will be returned in the response;
- `ONLY`—only FBP shipments will be returned;
- `WITHOUT`—all shipments except FBP will be returned.

Default value is `ALL`.

cancellation_type.description:
Cancellation type:
- `seller`—canceled by seller;
- `client` or `customer`—canceled by customer;
- `ozon`—canceled by Ozon;
- `system`—canceled by system;
- `delivery`—canceled by shipping provider.

available_actions.description:
Available actions and shipment information:
- `arbitration`: open a dispute;
- `awaiting_delivery`: set to the "Awaiting shipping" status;
- `can_create_chat`: start a chat with the customer;
- `cancel`: cancel shipment;
- `click_track_number`: view history of status changes using the tracking number in the personal account;
- `customer_phone_available`: customer phone number;
- `has_weight_products`: shipment contains products sold by weight;
- `hide_region_and_city`: hide the customer region and city in the report;
- `invoice_get`: get information from the invoice;
- `invoice_send`: create invoice;
- `invoice_update`: edit invoice;
- `label_download_big`: download large label;
- `label_download_small`: download small label;
- `label_download`: download label;
- `non_int_delivered`: set to the "Presumably delivered" status;
- `non_int_delivering`: set to the "In transit" status;
- `non_int_last_mile`: set to the "Courier is on the way" status;
- `product_cancel`: cancel some of the products in the shipment;
- `set_cutoff`: you need to specify the shipping date, use the [/v1/posting/cutoff/set](#operation/PostingAPI_SetPostingCutoff) method;
- `set_timeslot`: change the time of delivery to the customer;
- `set_track_number`: specify or change the tracking number;
- `ship_async_in_process`: shipment is being assembled;
- `ship_async_retry`: reassemble the shipment after an assembly error;
- `ship_async`: assemble shipment;
- `ship_with_additional_info`: fill in the additional information;
- `ship`: assemble shipment;
- `update_cis`: change additional information.

is_multibox.description:
Indication that there is a multi-box product in the shipment and you need to pass the number of boxes for it:

- `true`: before packaging pass the number of boxes using the [/v3/posting/multiboxqty/set](#operation/PostingAPI_PostingMultiBoxQtySetV3) method;
- `false`: you packed the shipment specifying the number of boxes in the `multi_box_qty` parameter, or there is no multi-box product in the shipment.

prr_option.description:
Lifting service code:
- `lift`: carrying the bulky product using the elevator;
- `stairs`: carrying the bulky product upstairs;
- `none`: the customer canceled the service, you don't need to lift the shipment;
- `delivery_default`: delivery is included in the price. According to the offer you need to deliver products to the floor.

The parameter is only relevant for bulky products with a delivery by a third-party or integrated service.

